# Real-World System Upgrade: Roles, Backend API, & Traveler Profiles

This implementation plan outlines the architectural steps necessary to upgrade the prototype into a fully functioning, real-world border control application. 

This brings in three major pillars: **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)**, **Live Backend Data Integration**, and a dedicated **Traveler Profile & Search** module.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This upgrade will transition the application from using static "mock" data to actually talking to your Node.js/PostgreSQL backend located at `ics-backend`. Please review the scope below and approve the plan to begin execution.

## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. Real-World API Integration
To behave like a production system, the frontend must stop using hardcoded data and start dispatching network requests to your database.

#### [MODIFY] `src/config/api.js` (NEW FILE)
- Create a central Axios/Fetch utility pointing to `http://localhost:5000/api` to streamline network calls and handle authentication headers.

#### [MODIFY] `ics-backend/server.js`
- Expand the Express backend to include robust API routes:
  - `POST /api/auth/login` - Validate credentials and return a session token + role.
  - `GET/POST /api/users` - Admin endpoints to manage staff accounts.
  - `GET /api/travelers/:passport` - Retrieve a specific traveler's chronological entry/exit footprint.

---

### 2. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
We will introduce strict permission boundaries across the application using an `AuthContext`.

- **Administrator Accounts:** Full system override. Unrestricted access to Dashboard statistics, Global Reports, and exclusive access to a new **User Management** portal to provision or revoke staff credentials.
- **Supervisor Accounts:** Management access scoped to a specific border point. Can view Dashboards, aggregate local Reports, and Process travelers, but cannot manage users.
- **Officer Accounts:** Strictly field-level access. Locked into the `Processing` scanner and the `Traveler History` lookup tools. Cannot view Settings, high-level Reports, or overall Dashboards.

#### [NEW] `src/context/AuthContext.jsx`
- Maintain the active user session persistently.

#### [NEW] `src/pages/UserManagement.jsx`
- Build a secure internal dashboard (accessible only to Administrators) rendering a directory of active staff, their designated roles, and an interface to securely onboard new agents.

---

### 3. Traveler History & Profile Lookup
To execute proper border security, agents require the ability to audit an individual's historical footprint.

#### [NEW] `src/pages/TravelerSearch.jsx`
- Design a high-security search gateway where Agents input a Document Number (MRZ) or Passport.

#### [NEW] `src/pages/TravelerProfile.jsx`
- Build a dedicated visual dossier page displaying a scanned traveler's identity card.
- Incorporate a chronological timeline component rendering every known border crossing (Exit/Entry), timestamps, associated Agent IDs, and historical Watchlist flags tied to that specific passport.

